#Text=Erosion is a hydraulic action, derived from the energy of running water.
#Text=Basin morphometry is a function of stream order and drainage patterns.
#Text=An iceberg is a piece of ice that has broken from an ice shelf and that floats in the Ocean.
#Text=Abrasion is a particle-by-particle erosion process and produces large amounts of silt-sized (0.002 - 0.0625 mm) sediments.
#Text=An aquifer is defined as a body of rock or unconsolidated sediment that has sufficient permeability to allow water to flow through it.
#Text=The term arenite applies to a so-called clean sandstone, meaning one with less than 15% silt and clay.
#Text=A periglacial environment is defined as any place where the geomorphic processes related to the freezing of water occurs.

#Text=A bay is a water body having a baymouth less than 24 nautical miles wide and an area that is equal to or greater than the area of a semicircle whose diameter is equal to the width of the baymouth
#Text=An isolated system is a system that is completely cut off from its surroundings and that cannot therefore import or export matter or energy.
#Text=A fault is a fracture along which movement associated with an earthquake has taken place, one side of the fault moving differentially to the other side.

#Text=Honeycomb weathering is a term used to describe numerous small pits or alveoli, no more than a few centimetres wide and deep, separated by an intricate network of narrow walls and resembling a honeycomb.
#Text=Tectonic denudation is a term that describes the unloading of mountains by gravity sliding and spreading.
#Text=Permafrost is soil or rock that remains frozen for two or more consecutive years.
#Text=A ground moraine is a blanket of mixed glacial sediments - mainly tills and other diamictons - formed beneath a glacier.
#Text=A coral reef is a ridge or mound built of the skeletal remains of generations of coral animals, upon which grow living coral polyps.
#Text=An atoll is a ring of coral reef and small sandy islands that encircles a shallow lagoon.
#Text=Weathering is a process of a slow continuous breakdown of rocks into smaller particles that are in equilibrium with the prevailing environment
#Text=Soil is a mixture of fine mineral fragments (including quartz and clay minerals), organic matter, and empty spaces that may be partially filled with water.
#Text=A clast is a fragment of rock or mineral, ranging in size from less than a micron (too small to see) to as big as an apartment block.
#Text=The term preglacial landform refers to any landform older than a specified glaciation.
